{"word":"Ἀδάμ","slug":"Ἀδάμ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>Ἀδάμ, ὁ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Heb.\">Heb.</a>] <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ indecl.\">indecl.</a> <b><i>Adam</i> <a href='B:520 5:14'>Ro 5:14</a>; <a href='B:530 15:22'>1 Cor 15:22</a>; <a href='B:610 2:13'>1 Ti 2:13</a>; <a href='B:720 1:1'>Jd 14</a>;</b> called <i>son of</i> <i>God</i> <b><a href='B:490 3:38'>Lk 3:38</a>.</b> In <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ transf.\">transf.</a> sense, of Christ <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὁ\">ὁ</a> <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἔσχατος\">ἔσχατος</a></el> (as opposed to <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:πρῶτος\">πρῶτος</a></el>) <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:Ἀδάμ\">Ἀδάμ</a></el> <i>the last Adam</i> <b><a href='B:530 15:45'>1 Cor 15:45</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀγωνίζομαι\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀδάπανος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}